library(stats)
#Reading the dataset
df<-read.csv("4063Midterm.csv")
df <- subset(df , City == "Toronto")
df <- select(df, "EdYears", "Cosmatics")
head(df)
#Question One
fviz_nbclust(df, hcut, method = "silhouette")

#Question Two
hc <- hclust(dist(df), "cen")
# Cut tree into 2 groups: 
sub_grp <- cutree(hc, k = 2)
# Create plot of clusters: 
fviz_cluster(list(data = df, cluster = paste0("Group", sub_grp)), 
             alpha = 1, 
             palette = "jco", 
             labelsize = 9, 
             ellipse.type = "norm") 

#Question Three
fviz_nbclust(df, kmeans, method = "silhouette")

#Question 4

km.res <- kmeans(df, 2, nstart = 10)
fviz_cluster(km.res, df, ellipse.type = "norm")

#Question Five #The hierarchical cluster model is better than Kmeans cluster model in clustering
